FBIS4-4967 "dreas066_c_94033" FBIS-EAS-94-066 Daily Report 5 Apr 1994 North Korea WPK Group Leaves for Greece; Arts Troupes Arrive WPK Group Leaves for Greece; Arts Troupes Arrive SK0504231794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1515 GMT 5 Apr 94 SK0504231794 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, April 5 (KCNA) -- A delegation of the Workers' Party of Korea headed by vice department director of the WPK Central Committee Pak Kyong-son left here today to participate in the Third Congress of the Panhellenic Socialist Movement of Greece. Malaysian musicians, Mongolian art and acrobatic groups, a Bangladesh art group, a Chinese acrobatic group, a Colombian musician and Vietnamese musicians came here today to participate in the 12th April spring friendship art festival. Also arriving here today was a delegation of the Kim Chong-suk kindergarten in Dalandzadgad City, Omnogov Province, Mongolia, led by its superintendent Altantuya.
